{"_id":"9uFVAWuGagRA2DMw","name":"Friend of the Rabbits","type":"gift","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/rabbit-corgi-green-purple.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","contentKey":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.friend-of-the-rabbits","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1,"folderName":"Wonderbedlam"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have earned the trust of the White Rabbits that carry messages throughout Wonder's impossible architecture. These magical creatures no longer fear you and will approach you willingly. You receive 2 Additional Successes when you attempt to capture or interact with a White Rabbit (reducing the Threat effectively to trivial difficulty). Once you've picked up a White Rabbit and gained its trust, your new little friends will deliver messages for you to any room in Wonder, even through seemingly closed doors, walls, or impossible distances. The rabbits can navigate Wonder's reality-bending structure instinctively, reaching locations that might be inaccessible to Hunters. You can send messages to allies separated in different Cure Rooms, communicate with Hatta Carter in the Basement, or even deliver warnings to Alice Liddell in the Hall of the Mind. The rabbits return to you after delivering their message, bringing back simple yes/no responses or brief replies (up to one sentence) from the recipient.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Wonderbedlam","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Wonderbedlam","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.friend-of-the-rabbits","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332115,"modifiedTime":1784280332115,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"A0AJutyCQph26kNN","name":"Lucid Madness","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-tendrils-pink-purple.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","contentKey":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.lucid-madness","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2,"folderName":"Wonderbedlam"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>After being subjected to Wonder's reality-bending magic, you have begun to understand how madness can be made real. You are slowly figuring out how to make the weirdest ideas manifest through Wonder's impossible architecture. Once per Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to attempt to activate the mad magic of Wonder for your own purposes. State something crazy that you want to accomplish, such as 'I want to walk on walls and ceiling', 'I want my arm to stretch out of proportion to reach that ledge', 'I want to shrink down to fit through that tiny door', 'I want doors to appear where there are only walls', or 'I want time to flow backwards for a moment'. The Storyteller will ask you to make a Position Check with Opposition Level determined by the madness of your request: **OL Easy 3** for minor impossibilities (walking on walls, glowing in the dark), **OL Medium 5** for moderate madness (stretching limbs, changing size), **OL Hard 7** for major reality warping (creating doors, manipulating time, phasing through walls). If you succeed, you gain a temporary Descriptor representing your declared impossibility for the rest of the Scene. If you fail, you have spent your Soma in vain and nothing happens. The effect immediately ends if someone makes it clear that what you are doing is utter madness—doubt and disbelief shatter the effect.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Wonderbedlam","somaCost":1,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Wonderbedlam","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.lucid-madness","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332116,"modifiedTime":1784280332116,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zQVO3qlJEbbBcaLe","name":"The Forgotten Queen","type":"gift","img":"icons/equipment/head/crown-thorns-gold-purple.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","contentKey":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.the-forgotten-queen","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3,"folderName":"Wonderbedlam"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>**SPECIAL GIFT FOR REGINA THE THIEF OF HEARTS ONLY.** Confusing flashbacks and painful emotions grip your mind as you explore Wonder. You've been here before as a patient, but the memories are fragmented and unclear. Something terrible happened to you in this place, something Alice Liddell tried to erase. Are you sure you want to remember? Once per Scene, you can attempt to remember something from your forgotten time in Wonder. Choose a specific place (Rabbit Hole, Labyrinth of Doors, Caterpillars' Greenhouse, Basement, Hall of the Mind) or a specific subject (Alice, Hatta, Cheshire, a Patient, the White Rabbits, Wonder itself). The Storyteller will give you one piece of useful information about that place or subject: a hidden Descriptor, a secret Gift they possess, their true Agenda, a weakness, or a crucial detail about how they function. This insider knowledge can be invaluable for navigating Wonder and confronting Alice. However, remembering is intensely painful—these are memories Alice tried to destroy for a reason. For the rest of the Scene after remembering, whenever you use one of your own Gifts, roll 1 die. On a result of 5 or 6, you lose 1 Soma as the mental strain overwhelms you, and you are no longer so sure that you are the Queen. Your identity begins to fragment and blur, just as Alice intended.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Wonderbedlam","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Wonderbedlam","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.the-forgotten-queen","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332116,"modifiedTime":1784280332116,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
